data.enText: involving two groups of people or two countries

data.chText: 双边关系 / 协议 / 贸易 / 谈判
（身体部位）两侧的，对称的；（大脑）两半球的
data.enText: involving both of two parts or sides of the body or brain

simple_means.memory_skill: bi 二 + later 侧面，边 + al …的 → 双边的

tr: affecting or undertaken by two parties
example: a bilateral agreement between the United States and Japan

tr: having identical parts on each side of an axis

value.def: Bilateral negotiations, meetings, or agreements, involve only the two groups or countries that are directly concerned.

example.tran: 英国和美国之间的双边会谈

example.ex: Disputes and differences between the two neighbours would be solved bilaterally.
example.tran: 两个邻国之间的争端和分歧应当通过双边途径解决。
